Citations
Date: 30/4/1910
Source: NZ Truth
Author:
Vol / Page: 23/4/8
Edition:
Quote: There is no `Police Court' in New Zealand, although the term is frequently used. The point was referred to by Mr. Salmond, Solicitor-General, in the Court of Appeal at Wellington recently. He said that a `Magistrate's Court' is known to the law, but not a police court. `A Justice of the Peace has no court,' he added.
